Bring him in before he wrecks that car
and we don't finish!

1472
02:11:49,810 --> 02:11:51,166
Bring him in, Shelby!

1473
02:11:51,319 --> 02:11:54,483
Or I will get you banned
from the SCCA and the FIA.

1474
02:11:55,943 --> 02:12:00,157
Ken Miles is behind the wheel, Leo.
That's his car to the finish.

1475
02:13:35,229 --> 02:13:37,470
Come on, lads. Where are you?

1476
02:13:48,167 --> 02:13:49,824
What's he doing?

1477
02:13:50,403 --> 02:13:52,714
Mom, why is he slowing down?

1478
02:14:24,340 --> 02:14:26,780
The 3 Fords are going to
cross the line together.

1479
02:14:27,044 --> 02:14:29,212
Ken Miles slowed down.
He waited for them.

1480
02:14:29,446 --> 02:14:31,972
Dad? No.

1481
02:14:32,107 --> 02:14:33,039
- It's all right.
- Dad.

1482
02:14:33,039 --> 02:14:35,440
It's all right. He's bringing them in.

1483
02:14:35,440 --> 02:14:36,501
<i>...Lead by Ken Miles...</i>

1484
02:14:36,501 --> 02:14:39,463
- He's bringing them all in together.
- <i>He's certainly the leader of this group.</i>

1485
02:14:40,420 --> 02:14:42,059
Good for you.

1486
02:14:42,692 --> 02:14:44,427
Good for you, Ken.

1487
02:15:11,698 --> 02:15:13,462
Look at that!

1488
02:15:15,215 --> 02:15:16,812
Well done, Leo.

1489
02:15:37,129 --> 02:15:40,414
Explain to me how he's finished first
if he's not won the race?

1490
02:15:40,460 --> 02:15:44,520
Because McLaren started from further,
so he came into and he won.

1491
02:15:44,579 --> 02:15:46,080
It's not a tie!

1492
02:15:46,406 --> 02:15:51,455
Because McLaren started further back, they're saying. He's
traveled a little bit further. So, he's won and not Ken.

1493
02:15:51,455 --> 02:15:53,233
That's bullshit!

1494
02:15:53,373 --> 02:15:55,351
Shel! Hold on!

1495
02:16:09,394 --> 02:16:12,194
Where is the tie?
Where is the goddamn tie?

1496
02:16:12,318 --> 02:16:13,289
What?

1497
02:16:13,539 --> 02:16:14,438
You son of a bitch!

1498
02:16:15,051 --> 02:16:16,403
- You knew!
- I didn't, I swear.

1499
02:16:16,403 --> 02:16:17,901
Enough!

1500
02:16:20,419 --> 02:16:22,672
Nice race, mate. Cograts.

1501
02:16:44,401 --> 02:16:46,093
Shel!

1502
02:16:50,037 --> 02:16:51,736
They robbed you, Ken.

1503
02:16:51,736 --> 02:16:56,064
<i>Here's the clarification. Both the
drivers finished the race in a heat.</i>

1504
02:16:56,198 --> 02:16:59,670
<i>McLaren has been ruled the winner
as he started from further back.</i>

1505
02:16:59,670 --> 02:17:02,198
Some bullshit technicality.

1506
02:17:15,366 --> 02:17:17,407
I never should've asked you.

1507
02:17:23,026 --> 02:17:25,177
Selling ties, yeah?

1508
02:17:27,457 --> 02:17:29,213
That's what they do.

1509
02:17:31,266 --> 02:17:33,739
You promised me the drive,

1510
02:17:35,878 --> 02:17:37,842
not the win.

1511
02:17:38,342 --> 02:17:40,441
It was a hell of a drive.

1512
02:17:40,967 --> 02:17:42,895
She's a hell of a machine.

1513
02:17:43,353 --> 02:17:45,047
She's fast.

1514
02:17:46,482 --> 02:17:48,254
Could be faster.

1515
02:17:49,799 --> 02:17:52,371
The 7 liters sweet.

1516
02:17:54,132 --> 02:17:59,637
We still need a lighter chassis.
I was thinking bonded aluminum.

1517
02:17:59,733 --> 02:18:05,591
It's a ground up rebuild, but if it works
we can lose a couple of hundred pounds.

1518
02:18:05,739 --> 02:18:07,757
What the hell are we doing here?

1519
02:18:09,081 --> 02:18:11,481
Let me take the shower,
get a cup of tea.

1520
02:18:11,630 --> 02:18:13,388
Have a sandwich or something.

1521
02:18:14,010 --> 02:18:16,408
We gonna get the bastards the next year.

1522
02:18:40,241 --> 02:18:42,801
Got a bit of fuel left in the tank.

1523
02:18:43,754 --> 02:18:47,716
What do you think of those honeycomb
panels. What you were looking for?

1524
02:18:47,716 --> 02:18:50,093
I don't know yet.

1525
02:19:14,467 --> 02:19:16,907
She looks pretty good.

1526
02:19:26,548 --> 02:19:30,304
There's a point at 7000 RPM

1527
02:19:31,425 --> 02:19:34,040
where everything fades.

1528
02:19:36,031 --> 02:19:41,105
The machine becomes weightless.
Just disappears.

1529
02:19:42,523 --> 02:19:47,598
And all that left is a body
moving through space and time.

1530
02:19:50,355 --> 02:19:55,583
7000 RPM, that's where you meet it.

1531
02:19:56,991 --> 02:20:01,759
You feel it coming.
It creeps up on you, close in your ear,

1532
02:20:09,280 --> 02:20:14,099
and asks you a question.
The only question that matters.

1533
02:20:22,157 --> 02:20:24,316
"Who are you"?

1534
02:20:57,450 --> 02:20:58,541
What do you think?

1535
02:20:58,541 --> 02:21:03,177
It's fantastic!
That was really good. Nice and smooth.

1536
02:21:04,145 --> 02:21:06,405
No vibration in the box.
She's really strong.

1537
02:21:06,405 --> 02:21:10,970
You drove her for less than an hour.
You can't tell shit after an hour.

1538
02:21:14,262 --> 02:21:16,195
Hey, Shel.

1539
02:21:25,562 --> 02:21:31,142
Hey, Shell. That guy, the one in the hat.
He's ready to close on those two 427's.

1540
02:21:31,215 --> 02:21:37,236
His and hers. Full freight.
They flew in from Galveston.

1541
02:21:41,018 --> 02:21:44,142
I need you to come outside
for maybe a minute.

1542
02:21:44,598 --> 02:21:46,407
And do what?

1543
02:21:47,701 --> 02:21:49,712
Be Carroll Shelby.

1544
02:21:50,222 --> 02:21:53,082
Tell them a story.
Spin a few magic words.

1545
02:21:53,474 --> 02:21:56,492
What does that mean? Magic words?

1546
02:21:57,468 --> 02:22:03,189
It means, come outside, and say hello, and
make them feel good about their purchase.

1547
02:22:03,189 --> 02:22:06,665
They're getting the damn cars.
That's what they get for their money, Phil.

1548
02:22:06,791 --> 02:22:09,761
Either they want them or they don't.
Am I some kind of a lounge act?!

1549
02:22:09,877 --> 02:22:12,545
Am I here to talk people into things?!

1550
02:22:23,351 --> 02:22:25,849
It's been 6 months, Shel.

1551
02:22:26,666 --> 02:22:28,748
Six months.

1552
02:22:32,731 --> 02:22:35,578
Sometimes, they don't get
out of the car.

1553
02:23:10,405 --> 02:23:12,252
Peter!

1554
02:23:12,705 --> 02:23:15,288
Peter, come and take the garbage out!

1555
02:23:15,288 --> 02:23:17,452
Mr. Shelby?

1556
02:23:18,452 --> 02:23:20,020
Hello, Pete.

1557
02:23:21,693 --> 02:23:23,749
I remember that wrench.

1558
02:23:24,481 --> 02:23:26,302
My Dad threw it at you.

1559
02:23:27,571 --> 02:23:29,336
I believe he did.

1560
02:23:29,771 --> 02:23:31,062
Why?

1561
02:23:35,905 --> 02:23:38,375
I think I probably
said something to him.

1562
02:23:39,014 --> 02:23:40,797
Called him a few names.

1563
02:23:42,559 --> 02:23:44,373
That's right.

1564
02:23:52,841 --> 02:23:55,016
Do you wanna speak to my Mom?

1565
02:23:55,141 --> 02:24:00,417
I did. I came to say hello
and check in on her.

1566
02:24:04,899 --> 02:24:07,697
Then, I started thinking that sometimes

1567
02:24:09,494 --> 02:24:16,416
the words just are not useful.

1568
02:24:22,125 --> 02:24:26,952
Tools are useful 'cause you can make stuff
with 'em, and you can fix stuff with 'em.

1569
02:24:27,750 --> 02:24:29,243
Here.

1570
02:24:30,179 --> 02:24:31,840
Thanks.

1571
02:24:39,973 --> 02:24:42,477
Your Daddy was a...

1572
02:24:45,134 --> 02:24:47,593
He was your friend.

1573
02:24:53,011 --> 02:24:54,935
Yes, he was.

1574
02:24:55,699 --> 02:24:57,441
Yes, sir.

1575
02:25:02,230 --> 02:25:05,665
And he thought
you were just finer than frog fur.

1576
02:25:09,552 --> 02:25:11,268
Peter!

1577
02:25:16,337 --> 02:25:18,805
I think I've gotta go help my Mom.

1578
02:25:20,540 --> 02:25:23,506
What are you doing here then? Go on.

1579
02:25:23,862 --> 02:25:25,946
Bye.

1580
